HEADWORD: Nervimotion
<hw>Ner`vi*mo"tion</hw> <pr>(n⟦etil⟧r`v⟦icr⟧*m⟦omac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Nerve</ets> + <ets>motion</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The movement caused in the sensory organs by
external agents and transmitted to the muscles by the nerves.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

